node.text:
Some friends are really there for you when you need them. And moreover, they are there for you with a resplendent roasted broccoli salad recipe. That's right, we said "resplendent' and WE MEAN IT. And please don't let the salad part deter you from the bacon and shallots, the sourdough croutons, and the bright lemon zest. This roasty sheet pan wonder is waiting to fill you up, any meal of the week.⠀
⠀
New on the blog! --> https://pinchofyum.com/roasted-broccoli-salad⠀

Honestly, it's almost embarrassing how easy this one is. But that is the SOS life we live! This One-Pan Farro is cozy, rustic, super wholesome - plus, it's packed with loads of flavor and brightness. There's fresh torn basil. There are, of course, sprinkles of parm. There's just a whole lot of yum in that one humble little pot.⠀

We're back with more life-saving SOS recipes because, okay, everything still needs to be easierrrrrrrr, you know? Low maintenance, minimal ingredients, max-i-mum flavor. These Tofu and Brown Rice Lettuce Wraps with peanut sauce and spicy mayo (and little crispy onions on top, of couuurse) are so delicious and filling and full of crunchy and creamy and saucy and spicy and we really do love them so.⠀
⠀
